text: We had a good family time. Cutlery was fresh, clean and looked new. Great ambience! Matching tasting of food items. Wide variety of Indian foods!

My 2nd time here with family. Good South Indian food. 1st time was South Indian meals.. now Had their Jeeraga samba briyani and an egg fried rice for the kid. Both were less oily as per our request. Best part was the South Indian filter coffee which, in my view, is the best we had so far. Even beats the A2B version at Little India. Will come back for sure for the coffee and South Indian food.
I really enjoy the food and atmosphere at this place. Itâ€™s clean, not crowded, and offers great value for money. The handmade ice cream is a must-try!

Ordered the ceylon parotta and filter coffee

There is a refined skill to the food and drinks made

Coffee was made was good beans and has the right kind of kick to it - fragrant and smooth

Parotta was prepared very well with plentiful flavours

15% discount on weekdays

This place should be on a Michelin star!
Excellent Indian food. The staff were really attentive and friendly too.
